# 🌐 Bootstrap Project

This is a responsive website built using **Bootstrap 5**. The project demonstrates how to use Bootstrap's grid system, components, and utilities to create a modern and mobile-friendly web layout.

## 📌 Features
- ✅ Fully responsive design  
- ✅ Built with Bootstrap 5  
- ✅ Clean and minimal UI  
- ✅ Easy to customize  

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- **HTML5**  
- **CSS3**  
- **Bootstrap 5**  
- (Optional) **JavaScript** for interactivity

## 🚀 Getting Started
1. Clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/bootstrap-project.git
Navigate to the project folder:


cd bootstrap-project
Open index.html in your browser to view the project.

🔗 Bootstrap CDN
This project uses Bootstrap via CDN.
Add this to the <head> of your HTML file:


![Website Screenshot](images/screenshot.png)






html
<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>